      <section eId="sec_906">
        <num>906</num>
        <heading>Driver's license verification; data retention</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_906__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a valid New York driver's license which authorizes the driver to\noperate vehicles of the class of the shared vehicle;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_906__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>a valid driver's license issued by the state or country of the\ndriver's residence which authorizes the driver in such state or country\nto drive vehicles of the class of the shared vehicle and is the age\nrequired of a New York resident to operate that class of vehicle; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_906__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>being otherwise specifically authorized by a valid license to\noperate vehicles of the class of the shared vehicle.\n  2. A peer-to-peer car sharing program administrator shall keep a\nrecord of:\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_906__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the name and address of the shared vehicle driver;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_906__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the identification number of the driver's license of the shared\nvehicle driver and each other person, if any, who shall operate the\nshared vehicle; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_906__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the date and place of issuance of the driver's license for each\nsuch vehicle operator.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
